<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910821-0029</DOCNO><DOCID>910821-0029.</DOCID><HL>   Technology Brief -- Smith Corona Corp.:   Shipments of New Line   Of Word Processor Delayed</HL><DATE>08/21/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4</SO><CO>   C.ACE SCO</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>COMPUTERS AND INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY (CPR)OFFICE EQUIPMENT (OFF)</IN><RE>CONNECTICUT (CT)FAR EAST (FE)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)TAIWAN (TW)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Smith Corona Corp. said shipments of its new personalword-processor line, originally scheduled for late August toOctober, will be delayed about six weeks.   In March the New Canaan, Conn., maker of electronictypewriters and word processors said it would introduce sevenmachines aimed at the home-computer user and priced from$1,000 to $1,900.</LP><TEXT>   These computers, tailored for the first-time user, aremade by Acer Inc., a Taiwan-based PC maker.   &quot;The operating architecture is totally new, and delays incompleting the final software feature programs have caused usto hold shipment until the entire program is complete,&quot; thecompany said. &quot;The trade is excited by our new products,&quot; itasserted, &quot;and our order rate has exceeded our expectations.&quot;   Smith Corona said the delay will affect results for itsfirst quarter, ending Sept. 30, as well as inventory levels.The company said it will reschedule introductoryadvertisements and shipments.   ---   Corrections andamp; Amplifications                                                                                                          SMITH CORONA Corp. said shipments of new personal wordprocessors will be delayed about six weeks. Yesterday'sedition incorrectly said the delay involved its new line ofpersonal computer products.   (WSJ Aug. 22, 1991)</TEXT></DOC>